{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/parse/options/record_delimiter/","result":{"data":{"page":{"html":"<h1 id=\"option-code-classlanguage-textrecord_delimitercode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#option-code-classlanguage-textrecord_delimitercode\" aria-label=\"option code classlanguage textrecord_delimitercode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Option <code class=\"language-text\">record_delimiter</code></h1>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">record_delimiter</code> option defines one or multiple characters used to delimit records.</p>\n<p>The value may be a string or a buffer or an array of both. It can not be empty. By defaults, the record delimiters are auto discovered. Supported auto discovery methods are Linux (<code class=\"language-text\">\\n</code>), Apple (<code class=\"language-text\">\\r</code>) and Windows (<code class=\"language-text\">\\r\\n</code>) record delimiters.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Type: <code class=\"language-text\">string|Buffer|[string|Buffer]</code></li>\n<li>Optional</li>\n<li>Default: <code class=\"language-text\">[]</code> (auto discovered)</li>\n<li>Since: 4.0.0</li>\n<li>Related: <a href=\"/parse/options/delimiter/\"><code class=\"language-text\">delimiter</code></a>, <code class=\"language-text\">quote</code>, <a href=\"/parse/options/escape/\"><code class=\"language-text\">escape</code></a> — see <a href=\"/parse/options/#available-options\">Available Options</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>It is not possible to escape a record delimiter. A field must be quoted if it contains a record delimiter which should not be interpreted as such.</p>\n<h2 id=\"history\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#history\" aria-label=\"history permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>History</h2>\n<p>Before version 4.0.0, this option was named <code class=\"language-text\">rowDelimiter</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"automatic-discovery\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#automatic-discovery\" aria-label=\"automatic discovery permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Automatic discovery</h2>\n<p>When the <code class=\"language-text\">record_delimiter</code> option is not defined, the parser automatically discovers the record delimiter from the first one encountered in the source. Auto discovery only applies outside of quoted fields.</p>\n<p>The following record delimiters are recognized and tested in this order:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Platform</th>\n<th>Delimiter</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Windows</td>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">\\r\\n</code></td>\n<td>carriage return and line feed</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Unix / Linux</td>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">\\n</code></td>\n<td>line feed</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Apple (Mac OS 9 and earlier)</td>\n<td><code class=\"language-text\">\\r</code></td>\n<td>carriage return</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The Windows delimiter (<code class=\"language-text\">\\r\\n</code>) is tested before the legacy Apple delimiter (<code class=\"language-text\">\\r</code>) so that a <code class=\"language-text\">\\r\\n</code> sequence is never mistaken for a lone <code class=\"language-text\">\\r</code> followed by an empty line.</p>\n<p>Once a record delimiter is discovered, it is used for the remainder of the parsing. Subsequent records are expected to use the same delimiter; a different line ending appearing later in the source is not treated as a record delimiter.</p>\n<h2 id=\"single-value-record-delimiter\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#single-value-record-delimiter\" aria-label=\"single value record delimiter permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Single value record delimiter</h2>\n<p>In the <a href=\"https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv/blob/master/packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.js\">record delimiter example</a>, two characters <code class=\"language-text\">&amp;&amp;</code> separate records.</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight display-embed-file-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> assert <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"node:assert\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> parse <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"csv-parse/sync\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> data <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"a,b,c&amp;&amp;d,e,f\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> records <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">record_delimiter</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"&amp;&amp;\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nassert<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">deepStrictEqual</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>records<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"d\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre><div class=\"display-embed-file\"><a href=\"https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv/blob/master/packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.js\">./packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.js</a></div></div></p>\n<h1 id=\"array-of-record-delimiter-values\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#array-of-record-delimiter-values\" aria-label=\"array of record delimiter values permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Array of record delimiter values</h1>\n<p>Record delimiter can be made of <a href=\"https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv/blob/master/packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.array.js\">multiple values</a> when defined as an array:</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight display-embed-file-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> assert <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"node:assert\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> parse <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"csv-parse/sync\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> data <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"a,b,c&amp;&amp;d,e,f||h,i,j\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> records <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">record_delimiter</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"&amp;&amp;\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"||\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nassert<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">deepStrictEqual</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>records<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"d\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"h\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"i\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"j\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre><div class=\"display-embed-file\"><a href=\"https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv/blob/master/packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.js\">./packages/csv-parse/samples/option.record_delimiter.js</a></div></div></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Option record_delimiter","description":"Option \"record_delimiter\" indicates how to split a record into multiple fields.","keywords":["csv","parse","options","record_delimiter","separator","tsv","line break"]},"headings":[{"id":"history","depth":2,"value":"History"},{"id":"automatic-discovery","depth":2,"value":"Automatic discovery"},{"id":"single-value-record-delimiter","depth":2,"value":"Single value record delimiter"}],"fields":{"edit_url":"https://github.com/adaltas/node-csv-docs/edit/master/src/md/parse/options/record_delimiter.md","slug":"/parse/options/record_delimiter/"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["421902736"],"slicesMap":{}}